# Python (my-agent)

When editing or adding Python files:

1. **Format & lint**: Code must pass `ruff check .` and `ruff format .` (line length **100**, double quotes). The repo root `.flake8` matches this so editor Flake8 (if any) does not default to 79 characters.
2. **Types**: Run `mypy .` — prefer explicit annotations on public functions; avoid unnecessary `Any`.
3. **Imports**: Standard grouping (stdlib → third-party → local); rely on Ruff (`I`).
4. **Third-party libraries**: Do not invent APIs — if unsure, verify real imports in the repo or the package docs.
5. **After generating**: Say explicitly when the user should run `uv run ruff check . && uv run ruff format . && uv run mypy .`.

Avoid: trailing whitespace, unused imports, bare `except:`, and duplicating logic that already exists — reuse `AgentState`, `WorkflowStage`, and existing nodes when appropriate.
